Step Parent


James Wigan

Managing Director at London Thoroughbred Services Ltd.

                  London Thoroughbred Services Ltd. is an international bloodstock agency. The company buys and sells racehorses and breeding stocks. The also provide personal services to breeders. London Thoroughbred Services was founded in 1976 by James Wigan and is headquartered in Dorset, United Kingdom.                





 Educational Background



Modern History 


University of London

                  The University of London is a collegiate research university located in London, England, consisting of 18 constituent colleges, 10 research institutes and a number of central bodies. The nine largest institutions of the federal university, usually termed the colleges, are Birkbeck, Goldsmiths, King's College London, the London Business School, Queen Mary, Royal Holloway, SOAS, LSE and UCL. Formerly a constituent college, Imperial College London left the University of London in 2007.                





 Career History



Partner

                                    Current                


Lepe Partners LLP


                  Lepe Partners is an independent merchant bank focused on the media, internet and consumer sectors.                




Professional

                                    2006 - 2009                


TriGranit Development Corporation


                  TriGranit Fejlesztoi Kft provides real estate development services. It develops retail and entertainment centers, office buildings, hotels, residential buildings, waterfront resorts, and cultural facilities. The company was founded by Sándor Demján in 1995 and is headquartered in Budapest, Hungary.                




Professional

                                    2005 - 2006                


Hargreave Hale Ltd.


                  HHL is an active manager which manages the Hargreave Hale AIM Venture Capital Trusts 1&2, investing in a diversified portfolio of small UK-based companies on a high risk, medium-term capital growth basis.  They invest primarily in AIM-traded companies which have the opportunity for significant value appreciation and also invest in smaller companies which may not be readily accessible to private individuals, aiming to maximize distributions to shareholders from capital gains and income generated from the funds.  In addition, they invest in equities which are non-qualifying investments on an opportunistic basis. The firm invests in AIM companies, ISDX-quoted companies and private companies, sovereign debt, quasi-sovereign debt, bonds and other-fixed income securities and readily realizable bank deposits.                




Vice President & Partner

                                    Prior                


Monument Capital Group LLC


                  Monument Capital Group focuses primarily on investment opportunities within the homeland security and defense sectors. The firm originates, structures and makes direct equity investments in buyouts, strategic or control equity investments, equity private placements and growth capital financings. They look for companies with proven management teams and competitive advantages in technologies and/or services that meet the security needs of governmental and commercial entities. Monument Capital Group strives to accelerate the growth of their portfolio companies and facilitate their long-term success through: (1) operational improvements (2) the development of relationships with potential customers (3) the development of global alliances (4) the identification of new financing sources and (5) the recruitment of skilled executives as needed.Monument Capital Group also provides strategic advisory and investment services for those operating in the homeland security and defense sector. The firm provides services to Federal and select international governments. Their services include providing objective analysis of their operations and activities and assisting with proactive policy development and informed decision making. The firm also works with clients in the private sector including global technology providers and early-stage companies with innovative technologies and proven management teams. Monument Capital Group seeks to help these clients grow their businesses, identify partners and capital and build service and technology platforms. In addition, the firm provides a variety of investment services to clients in the financial and homeland/defense sector including: (1) strategic business advice (2) the facilitation of business partnerships (3) market assessments (4) the facilitation of new ventures and (5) governmental and program analysis.                




Risk Management Division

                                    Prior                


N.M. Rothschild & Sons Ltd.


                  N.M. Rothschild & Sons Ltd. provides banking and financial services. It offers investment and commercial banking, treasury, merchant banking, fund management, private banking and trust management services to governments, corporations and individuals. The company has operations in USA, Zimbabwe, South Africa, Switzerland, United Arab Emirates, Sweden, Turkey, Singapore, Russia and Spain. N.M. Rothschild & Sons was founded in 1809 and is headquartered in London, the United Kingdom.                




